{"id":22492264879,"name":"Run api tests","node_id":"WFR_kwLOA_1uaM8AAAAFPKS5rw","head_branch":"perf-user-creation","head_sha":"5e49b5d1b5bac708bdc52dc3b15edf70606847d7","path":".github/workflows/run-api-tests.yml","run_number":47466,"run_attempt":1,"event":"pull_request","display_title":"perf: Fix N+1 query problems when creating users with group membership","status":"completed","conclusion":"cancelled","workflow_id":5591308,"check_suite_id":58813596956,"check_suite_node_id":"CS_kwDOA_1uaM8AAAANsZBFHA","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/22492264879","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/22492264879","pull_requests":[{"id":3336200647,"number":23103,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/pulls/23103","head":{"ref":"perf-user-creation","sha":"64604a9ce850b7bb59e5d0622a7cbe186e10b219","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}},"base":{"ref":"master","sha":"1b310295495318bab3cc3cfb664ed319070ca0a2","repo":{"id":66940520,"name":"dhis2-core","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core"}}}],"created_at":"2026-02-27T15:25:52Z","updated_at":"2026-02-27T15:28:10Z","run_started_at":"2026-02-27T15:25:52Z","jobs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/22492264879/jobs","logs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/22492264879/logs","check_suite_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/check-suites/58813596956","artifacts_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/22492264879/artifacts","cancel_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/22492264879/cancel","rerun_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/runs/22492264879/rerun","head_commit":{"message":"perf: Fix N+1 query problems when creating users with group membership\n\nTwo independent N+1 query problems were identified that significantly\nslowed user creation in large DHIS2 instances.\n\n1. SchemaToDataFetcher loaded all records for uniqueness checking\n\nDuring preheat (which runs before every metadata import including\nAPI-driven user creation), SchemaToDataFetcher issued an unbounded\nquery to load ALL records of a given type to check for uniqueness\nconflicts. For a database with 221K users this meant a full table scan\non every user creation request. The fix scopes the query to only\nrecords whose unique property values match the objects being imported.\n\n2. Adding a user to a group loaded the entire group members collection\n\nDefaultUserGroupService.addUserToGroups was writing group membership\nthrough Hibernate's UserGroup.members collection (the owning side),\nforcing Hibernate to load all existing members before it could detect\nthe change and write to the join table. For a group with 42K members\nthis produces a 42K-row query per group the new user is assigned to.\nThe fix adds a direct SQL INSERT to HibernateUserGroupStore that writes\nto usergroupmembers without loading the members collection, with\ntargeted L2 cache eviction for User.groups and the UserGroup entity.\n\nPerformance results (Gatling, 3 iterations, group with ~42K members):\n- Mean response time: 2,009ms -\u003e 397ms (5x improvement)\n- p95 response time:  2,844ms -\u003e 621ms (4.6x improvement)\n- Throughput:         0.43rps -\u003e 1.5rps (3.5x improvement)\n\nNote: user deletion has a related N+1 in UserRoleDeletionHandler and\nUserGroupDeletionHandler that is not addressed here and will be covered\nin a separate PR.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","author":{"name":"Jason Pickering","email":"jason@dhis2.org"},"id":"5e49b5d1b5bac708bdc52dc3b15edf70606847d7","tree_id":"40ef19800af9b81a0690f789d07a42399d39f0e9","timestamp":"2026-02-27T15:24:11Z","committer":{"name":"Jason Pickering","email":"jason@dhis2.org"}},"workflow_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/workflows/5591308","repository":{"id